== News & Chronology ==

 * 2004-10-01 US [:SunKodak04En: Sun loses loses patent infringment lawsuit, Kodak asks for 1 bn damages for use of Java]
 * 2004-09-30 US [:JonathanSchwartzEn: Jonathan Schwartz]: [:Schwartz040930En: "I believe in IP"] -- Sun CEO in favor of patents for "all endeavors from drugs to academic work"
 * 2004-10-03 US [http://www.groklaw.net/article.php?story=20041003041632172 Groklaw: Kodak Wins Java Lawsuit Against Sun]; and [http://yro.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=04/10/03/1738230&tid=155&tid=1 Slashdot discussion]
 * 2004-10-02 US [http://yro.slashdot.org/yro/04/10/01/2246216.shtml?tid=102&tid=155 Slashdot: Sun Files For Patent on Software Licensing Method]
 * 2004-10-02 US [http://www.rbj.net/fullarticle.cfm?sdid=51946 Rochester Business Journal: Jurors find for Eastman Kodak in patent rights case against Sun] "Kodak is seeking some $1 billion in damages for infringements by Sun's lucrative Java software platform against three software patents the photo giant acquired from Wang Laboratories in 1997." [http://www.democratandchronicle.com/apps/pbcs.dll/article?AID=/20041002/BUSINESS/410020333/1001 Also in Rochester Democrat & Chronicle] "Software patents are just coming into vogue." [http://www.groklaw.net/article.php?story=20041003041632172 Groklaw comments].
 * 2004-09-30 [http://marketwatch-cnet.com.com/Suns+Schwartz+guns+for+patent+glories/2100-1014_3-5390714.html Schwartz guns]* 2004-09-13 US [http://www.rbj.net/fullarticle.cfm?sdid=51711 US$ 1 billion lawsuit from Kodak against Sun starts over 3 software patents Java allegedly infringes on]
 * 2004-09-16 US [http://story.news.yahoo.com/news?tmpl=story&ncid=1817&e=4&u=/cmp/20040917/tc_cmp/47212251&sid=96120750 Microsoft-Sun deal of April 2004 excludes OpenOffice users from protection against litigation] - See also [http://www.computerworld.com.au/index.php?id=1257037803 this on Computerworld] (--> [:MsSun0404En: MS Sun])
 * 2004-09-15 US Linux Electrons: [http://www.linuxelectrons.com/article.php/20040914141417417 Sun Sells Out Open Office to Microsoft] (cryptic report about a patent cross-licensing agreement between [:SwpatsunEn: Sun] and [:SwpatmicrosoftEn: Microsoft] which, according to the writers, comes close to a sale of !OpenOffice.org to Microsoft; [http://www.newsforge.com/article.pl?sid=04/09/15/213216 NewsForge] says it is not true)
 * 2004 spring: Sun distances itself from EICTA Pro-Patent statement, asks EICTA to add a note mentioning Sun as dissenter
 * 1998-2000? Sun is temporarily the company with the largest number of swpat applications at EPO
